[title]Critical point[title]

[date]01.09.2018[date]

[category]Company[category]

![Critical point](../img/blog/kritische_phase.png)

[description]
People don't like to mention it when things aren't going well. Ultimately, however, every successful entrepreneur can report on such phases. So why not talk about it openly? In contrary, it would be smarter if we just smiled.</br></br>

In 2018, several problems came together, such as a drop in sales in the second half of the year, bottlenecks in deliveries, discrepancies in partner companies, a lack of experience in management and unreliability among employees.</br></br>

“It's only after we've lost everything, that we're free to do anything!” -Tyler Durden
[description]
